attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is an IoT botnet malware that downloads and executes additional payloads. It propagates by exploiting a known remote code execution vulnerability in Huawei home gateways (CVE-2017-17215), indicated by the crafted SOAP request to `/ctrlt/DeviceUpgrade_1`. It downloads a second-stage payload from `89[.]213[.]193[.]98` using `wget` and executes it via a command injection payload. The binary also enumerates processes in `/proc` to kill competing malware or security tools.
